author: Old School Rocker
title: Nice set of buds....
content:
Received early. Quality packaging. No real (active) noise cancellation going on and none expected at this price point. No volume control/mic/track change, etc. (which is just what I wanted: no doo dads, no unnecessary queries with Siri, etc.>>>just a quality music listening device when you find yourself away from regular speakers). Size selection for ear pieces (s/m/l+ set of foams). Clip included (nice touch). And yes, the cords are thought out>nice and flat making them easier to keep straight and not tangle. Even a small drawstring carry pouch.  For the $, this is a nice set of basic buds..quality is everywhere and tolerances are tight..when you put the 3.5mm end onto your Apple dongle, you push firmly and then there is a noticeable click-no slop or sliding around, etc.
A mention on the ear buds and sizing: proper fit is critical for good sound-especially bass. Play around with not only how you put position the bud in your ear, but also the size of the ear piece fitted to the bud itself>if you don't have a good fit the bass will definitely be lacking..  Fitting the ear piece on/off the bud can be a tad challenging (those dang tight tolerances again), but worth the time to get it right-don't rush it. Recommended.

3. The cord is wide and flat, not thin and cylindrical. This is just a personal preference, but I did not like the way the cord felt.
4. Why spend this money. Either get a cheaper pair of cheap "noise canceling" earbuds, or spend more money for something that actually works. This is just a waste of money imo.

The bass is phenomenal. The sound quality is amazing for the price (I'd go as far as to say it's a steal). But yeah, my only complaint is there is no control on the wires.

title: Not super comfortable, very durable.
content: I like that these are very durable.  I took off and star because when I put them on snugly, and create a seal in my ear with them, it actually mutes the sound, so I have to put the buds in my ears loosely and they fall out more easily. Also, I have problems with the shape as I can't lay down with these on because they stick out of my ears too far and it pushes on them. They are noise cancelling; my husband has to yell my name to get my attention when I wear them. I also am not taking off any stars for this, but I didnt realize they don't have a mic or button on them.

author: Jessica C.
title: It is worth the price 100%

author: Denisse
title: Great sound but they have a heavy thing
content: Great sound, bass sounds spectacular! 100% noise concealing, thd only reason I gave it 1 star less is because it has a rectangular thing where the two headphones are separated that weights too much and is too heavy that pulls the headphones out of my ears until they pop out while I am jogging.  I don't know what is for but I can not take it  off.

author: PP
title: Amazing Price Amazing headphones! Buy these!
content: These are the best headphones you’ll buy. The price is amazing too!

author: Bill With. 40
title: Sounds great to me
content: At first I was a little disappointed with the base until I switched to the small tips.  Wow, now the base sounds excellent.  Not boomy but quality.  It is important to have a good fit to get the full base effect.  The mid tones and the highs are also as good.  When testing earphones or earbuds I usually go to one of my albums that has  good quality base, mids and highs.  This album is called Fourplay and the number is Max-O-Man.  With the proper fit this model is a pleasure and I am enjoying listening to all my favorite quality albums.  My ears are 78 yrs. old and if they sound good to me they should sound much better to younger ears.  It is said that earphones, earbuds and speakers have to break in before they give peak quality sound output and if these get any better ---WOW.

author: Noers
title: Trash
content: No idea why these are so highly-rated. Bass is garbage. Sound is flat. No volume control on the headphones, the cords going to each ear are unnecessarily long. Just stick with Skullcandy.

author: barry
title: I'm Loveing it
content: it's great

author: K. M.
title: The sound quality from these earphones is quite amazing
content: Prior to purchasing these earphones, I had another cheap set from a discount store that stopped working soon after I bought it. But even while it did work, the sound quality was not the best, but I was used to it. So I wasn't prepared for what I was about to hear when I tried these earphones. Wow! It's difficult to remember the sound quality I was hearing back when I had my old Surround Sound stereo, but to me, these earphones remind me of that stereo system again. Quite amazing! I hope these will last me a long time. I plan to update this review later to report how long they are lasting. But for the price, I don't think you can beat the sound you will get from these earphones.

author: Joe
title: clen clear sound, very pleasing.
content: workout at gym

author: deanie11
title: Great headphones
content: Great headphones for no more than they cost. Would purchase again.

author: T. Brown
title: These are the best earbuds under $20 period!!!
content: I've tried countless earbuds under $20 and some above that as well,but these I bought 3 pairs of them and they sound so good that I wanted backups. The bass response is perfect for my very wide variety of music that I listen to on my LG V20,the quad dac pushes them to deafening levels and  everything sounds very balanced,nothing sounds overpowered at all.  I've never heard such good sound from cheap earbuds,typically you'd have to spend at least $50 for the sound that these reproduce.

author: Leslie Michael
title: They’re better than most but not better than all
content: One side is louder than the other, not as comfortable to fall asleep with as others I’ve tried, and I can still hear dogs barking from a block away when they are in but it’s sooo much better than trying to sleep to music when dogs were barking before....they are priced right for what you get!

content: This did not work at all with my iPad Pro. No sound at all. The part that plugs into the iPad is different then what is shown in advertisement. This one only has two indented bands not three

author: CRH
title: Very disappointing.
content: I was excited about these earphones, they have lots of positive reviews.  They arrived quickly, are well packaged, look good, come with nice accessories, and have good sound quality- until I move my head.  I purchased them to use with a "silent guitar".  When I move my head or shift my body while playing the cord rubs against my shirt, or jacket, and the rubbing sound is quite noticeable through the headphones- definitely not what I was expecting.  The cord is a soft rubber and doesn't slide smoothly across anything with texture.  I tried using the clip that comes with the earphones, but that didn't help, I tried positioning the cord a couple of different ways- again without success.  I suppose if I jacked the volume up on the guitar, or played heavy metal, I might not notice the rubbing  sound, but its definitely there with finger picking. So, I'm returning them, though at a cost- I had to pay shipping both ways.

Would buy again ...

Solid earbuds while it lasted, though.

content: I love the sound quality and the headphones seem durable.  However, they do hurt my ears after prolonged use (more than 2 hours), but so do most earphones.  I would give these a try.  Nice price, too.

author: K. Smith
title: Unless you like Urgent Care, stay away from these!!!!
content: This item is cheaply made.  My teenage son put them in his ears and the soft part of the bus came off and was lodged in his ear.  An inexpensive bud for school turned into a 150.00 Urgent care visit to have it removed.  Do not buy!!!!!!

author: Matthew Callen
title: Good build and sound for the price
content: Metal phones and strong flat cable and connector. Good sound when fitted properly.

author: Amazon Customer
title: Great quality, presentation and extras
content: I was surprised to see a carrying case, high quality foam earbuds (along with various sizes of rubber earbuds) and generally high quality materials for a $12 pair of IEMs. Sounds great for the price and good isolation.

author: Ians
title: My mom loves them! 5 stars!
content:
Sent this pair abroad to my mom, arrived surprisingly fast with no issues whatsoever. Shipping company contacted my mom to schedule delivery, great service.
My mom is happy with them, she says it's very loud (she is almost deaf). Nice! Will prob buy a few more of these as spare if/when they break.

Update: July 2019
Bought 2 more pairs. This brand seem to be holding really nice. So I bought another pair to replace bad ones (were twice the price of this set).  Great earbuds for great price.

author: Paul Hitchcock
title: Awesome Product
content: I picked these up for the noise cancellation feature because I work on a mower cutting grass all day. The other headphones I have tried before these from Betron left a lot to be desired when it came to noise cancellation and sound quality. So, I ordered a pair and thought for the price I couldn't get hurt even if they weren't all that. They arrived in the two days allowed by my Prime membership and I was pleasantly surprised how well put together they are. They actually have some weight to them compared to comparable headphones. I used them fort he first time the next day when I started the mower up. WOW!! Not only did they cut the mower noise down to a whisper, the sound that comes from these headphones is amazingly loud with excellent quality. I am very happy with my purchase and highly recommend them to anyone searching for a great set of headphones. The only thing that makes these things any better is the price. Very economical. I will be purchasing more in the future as Christmas gifts.

author: Cordia Schmidt
title: Amazing quality for the price
content: I am blown away by the quality of sound that these headphones produce for the price. I just received them yesterday, so I can't speak to the longtime durability, but they definitely feel as though they will last for quite a while. They do a great job of blocking out the surrounding sounds as well. Definitely pleased with this purchase!

author: Amazon Customer
title: Good sound quality, but doesn't stay in my ears.
content: The sound quality is good, the cables are sturdy and indeed are tangle-free, and the earbuds are pretty. The one frustrating thing about these earbuds is that they don't stay in my ears, particularly when I run. The weight of the bouncing cables tends to make the earbuds fall out.

There is also 1 special replacement pad different from the rest with a different feel. I use them often but overtime, they start to come off and you have to put them back on constantly.

author: Jerry M.
title: Great sound from these Ear Buds
content:
These are really good ear buds for the price. I compared them to another pair of ear buds that were more than double
the price of these are these much better. This is the second pair of  Betron  ear buds I have purchased.  Other features
of DC950 I like are the tangle free cord, extra soft ear pieces, carrying bag. These ear buds are noise isolating, not noise
canceling, there is a difference. Noise canceling is active noise management by the ear buds themselves. Noise isolating
is like using ear protectors from loud noises.

author: Amelia Agueda
title: Great bass and sound quality
content: I use these at the gym and they are as promised. Great bass and good sound quality. They sound as good as my $70.00 pair of headphones.

author: Frank Moore III

author: M and K
title: Inexpensive and Good Quality
content:
Title says it all really. The sound quality is good, especially for the price. They feel well constructed, come with a number of varied earbud tips; including a sound canceling foam type that I haven't quite been able to keep in my ear solidly enough to make it work to it's full potential (I have pushed them and held them into place to see how well they will block noise, which they do quite effectively.), and also a clip to help hold the wires in a way as to prevent the earbuds from falling out due to wires being pulled from varying pull stressors, such as when the mp3 player is held in ones pants pocket and gentle but constant pull created from that scenario while walking or working. Flat sealed wires are seemingly far more resistant to tangling, though obviously not impervious to the curse. Overall, vary satisfied.

Keep in mind, I'm not an audio fanatic; so if you aren't one as well you most likely with be very satisfied with your purchase as it's comfy, solid, inexpensive, and outputs a good clean range of sound. If you're a Noise Marine though, these may not be for you.

author: Denver D
title: Great!
content: Whoa, not what I was expecting for ten dollars at all.  These are mighty little earbuds.  I ordered these when my last pair of earbuds died (an old pair of Apple earbuds), which I used for listening to music, etc., at work on my phone or computer.  With my old pair, I needed the master computer volume turned up all the way, and then the app volume at about 75% to listen comfortably.  Not these!  I turned the master volume down to 50% and the app volume at 50% for the same sound level.  Lots of sound out of these, with great bass and crisp high end.  The bass sometimes is TOO good and drowns out some of the midrange, but overall very good deal for ten bucks.

title: Sound was great, fit not so much.
content:
Sound was great, with crisp clean audio. Somewhat uncomfortable in my ears after a while despite trying different end-caps. Unable to attest to their longevity/continued performance since they were only in my possession 5 days.
Ultimately none of it mattered as my cat discovered them and happily chewed through the cord. Evidently, he really enjoys silicon cords? These were my 2nd set of replacements - I've since switched to (much) less expensive earbuds due to the cat.

author: Kapna
title: These earbuds are GREAT! Impressive for the Price and HIGH QUALITY sound
content:
I have gone through a lot of headphones. From $200 Bose (wired/wireless) to $100 Beats. But nothing beats the simple wired headphones. I produce music and listen to a lot of music and these earbuds do the trick.

If you're looking for simple headphones with high quality sharpness, these are the best for the price you are paying. The frequencies are all flat, so you get music and sound as its suppose to sound. Nothing on the Low end (Bass) is altered. And you can hear bass and all on these headphones. Very crisp and punchy sound. Does not sound cheap.

In fact, I can compare these earbuds to Sennheisers Earbuds which range from $75-$100... and they sound just as good almost the same.

... Think about that:
$10 Headphones = $100 Headphones

It comes with a nice bag to put them in and alternate ear pieces (Sm, Med, Larg). The packaging is impressive. It looks like you got expensive headphones.

Overall: If you don't want to spend more than $10-12 on good headphones these are awesome. I don't know about the longevity of them because I just got them. But I'll update the review once I see how long they last.

author: Big. W
title: awsome sound
content: I didn't expect the great quality of sound these have, there awesome!  I wish they had volume control , definitely would Recommend

author: Lawrence Underwood
title: The Sound is Amazing
content:
I have been through the gamut of earphones....including some of the top name brands such as; Apple, Sony, etc..
The Betron earphones are by far the BEST on the market...at an affordable price. It is rare that you find a product that is reasonable priced, that is exceptional. In my career, I have to do an incredible amount of documents, which require me to focus and not be disturbed by colleagues. The Betron earphones, provide me with a quality of sound that allows me to focus, not be disturbed and most importantly, makes it more relaxing and comfortable, to do clinical documentation, that is normally boring and monotonous. You will not be let down if you choose to purchase these earphones. Additionally, they are well made and durable, and come with a really nice bag. Well done!!

title: Great sound
content: They sound great!! Cord doesn't tangle (as stated), and they stay in my ear. Only complaint is that when I've had them on 45min or so, my ears start to hurt a little from the foam ear pads. They aren't gel- so not as comfy. But that can be fixed by changing them. Overall, very happy.  I just got them so don't know how long they'll last. Seem sturdy though.

author: Tiffani LL
title: Good headphones especially for the price
content: Really happy with these headphones. I have a busy commute on the train in the morning and evenings they really do cancel out all the noise. The bass boost is another extra bonus. This set doesn't have a mic which I prefer since the mics on these sort of headphones are not always great and I prefer to just talk into my phone anyway.  The fit could be better, but other than that it's a good deal.

They sound great when they're working.  But its frustrating when you're watching something and you have to rewind to hear what was said.

author: Dicecity

content: These earphones are as described and more. They have a very durable feel, very comfortable and they are a classy black and res color. I'm very happy with this product!

My husband is using the first (without) the microphone and really like the quality of sound.  He listens to audiobooks and the quality is outstanding.  I like the earphones with the microphone - convenient and the quality is outstanding.  Great purchase for sure.  Would definitely buy again as a gift, etc.

author: Bobby
title: Amazing Headphones
content:
The quality of these headphones are outstanding. The material used for the headphones are actually metal not plastic as the picture makes it look like plastic.
The sound quality of the headphones are just as amazing as the material. The sound of the music is so loud when turned half way on my Samasung J3 and cancels all other noise from outside them.
The headphones I received didn't have a volume controller on the wire, but I enjoy headphones without that feature anyhow and loved that they came with a carrier bag and clip for my shirt. Thank you for the amazing product and keep up the good work.

author: Al E.
title: Very good product
content: I use these while at the gym and they stay put while moving around a lot. Very clear and sounds are great.

author: RocketScience
title: Deep Heavy Bass, good sound for the price.
content: I bought these specifically to listen to music and bought another Betron model simultaneously that is also excellent.  Well made, non twist cord, feels quality, but most of all, good deep bass. The bass is a bit overdriven and does distort mid range and highs a little bit, so if you have music with heavy bass lines, it might dominate too much. However,  At this price, you can't beat these Betrons if you like heavy bass in earbuds.

author: Duan Carter
title: For the price, you can't beat'em
content:
I just needed some earphones for my computer at work. My Sony's started shorting out after 10 years. I gotta be honest, didn't want to invest more than $10. These Betron DC950's were well reviewed.

Let me say the positives first - they look good, feel o.k., and are solidly built.

The negatives - the sound is a'ight. Wasn't too worried about noise cancellation at this price point anyway. But I had some skull candy's at this price point many years ago that had better sound quality.

author: ProAudio
title: Lacking in middle/high range.
content:
Overall for the money, I guess I am happy enough. My experience with buds under $20 (that's all I buy!) is that perhaps 40% lack punchy bass, 40 % lack any presence or highs and 20% are absolutely flat and missing lows and highs.

However, I noticed that the efficiency seems to be higher than most of the other buds I have been using. At least a 6 db increase in volume over the Skull Candy and a few others.  Have not tested with equipment but I suspect that the power band is pretty flat across the entire spectrum.

I had been buying Skull candy Inkd around $12 and they would last about 9 months or so before I would destroy the connector etc.

The flat rubber cable used with the Betron DC950 appears to be pretty durable and preferable to the plastic leads used by most others.

For the money sonically I would give these a strong 4 plus. Mechanically also a 4.0
By the way, this was a second choice product for me. The Model I wanted to order was a Betron also. Special sale at about $13.95 (Amazon) YSM1000.

I took a phone call and to my dismay as went to finish my order the supply went to zero. a day a later I check again and that same set of earbuds was around $40!  YSM1000. Today now $13.95!

I wonder how they compare? Unfortunately, I can only budget for only about $15 a year for buds!

Virtually no clarity, indiscernible mids or highs. For the average listener this can be problematic ESPECIALLY if your music selection is not bass heavy. For classical, jazz, souls or adult contemporary music - these headsets will leave you woefully disappointed.
I've heard similarly inexpensive earphones that offered a much more balanced sound.
Would not recommend, keep looking.

title: Betron DC950 - Great product, great value
content: When I read reviews I look for the critical ones to see what problems consumers are experiencing.  To Beltron's credit, I don't have anything negative to say about these ear buds.  I only wish I had purchased the model with mic and vol control but my first buy was a test based on other reviews. So far these have been the highest quality earbuds I have ever purchased and at a fantastic price, and I have purchased other at a much higher price with worse quality.  I will purchase another pair or two from Betron as I hike a lot and use them constantly.  The selection of earbud jels and the inclusion of the noise isolation covers, the clip, and a product pouch for storage are only second to the tangle free cable, which it is, and the reason I purchased them. Obviously they can still wrap but they don't lock or tie themselves in a knot, so MUCH better than those I have used in the past.  Lastly, I use these buds for both music and movies, and while I am not an audiophile, to me the sound quality is very good!

Bought these for a friend, and he has been using them for well over a week now with his tablet! He says they've been of VERY decent quality, and he is very happy with them.

Pros:
Decent sound quality
Good price
Seemingly pretty durable
Come with a clip and a bag
Multiple nub sizes included for good fit

Cons:
No built in volume slider

That's pretty much the assessment of it, and the lack of volume slider hasn't really affected anything, unless you're using it with an app or game that makes it problematic to change volume.

Overall very happy with this buy!

author: Caryn
title: Tuned quite high
content:
I bought these as temporary replacements for my beloved earbuds that I accidentally sucked into the vacuum cleaner. The audio is clear, which is great for my transcription work. But they are super trebly; there is essentially no mid or low end. Some audio will pierce my ear because of the high pitch, so I'll have to turn the volume down even if it's not all the way up. For music, you will definitely want an equalizer. But there's no fuzz or buzz or distortion; they're very clear for the price, and the red and black looks pretty cool to me.
The buds are comfortable in the ears; I can wear them for hours at a time with no discomfort. I'm on the smallest size, but for my ears I could go one smaller. But they don't fall out, and I just push them in slightly when I need to hear something a little more closely.
Overall, they're great for the spoken word, but you'll want to get a bass booster or equalizer for your music. I'd recommend as a temporary replacement, backup, or travel pair.

author: Jerry S
title: Longevity
content:
Today was the first time I had used my Betron DC earphones.  Like everyone else, for the money, I was very happy with the sound quality.  Unfortunately, i am not convinced they will last one month.  Immediately I had to wiggle one of the cord lines because I wasn't getting sound through one ear.  It came back, but a second time it began to crackle.  So that part is disappointing and if you wish to purchase these, I would recommend investing in the protection plan.  If I get a year out of any earbuds I am extremely happy.  The Betron's come with a pouch, but I have started to always place my earphones/buds in a tupperware type small container.

I use to have brands that cost me over $100.  Neither lasted a year due to the cheap wiring.  Betron is no different, but placing other brands in a hard case seems to allow them to last longer.

author: JimS
title: PROS really outweigh the CONS
content: PROS:  One of the most frustrating things about the other ear buds I've purchased is the thin wires that are used.  They're destined to fail, and generally, it doesn't take long.  These ear buds haven't failed me after 4 months of heavy use.  Bought several more pairs as backups.  They sound good too.  While they're not noise cancelling, they do help to muffle background sounds.  Another plus is the extra ear cushions they come with (nice diameters!)  CONS:  If the angle of the buds in your ear changes , there can be dramatic changes to sound.  So if you are listening to something while sitting down or resting, great.  On the other hand, if you want to listen to something while cutting your grass, to avoid having to crank up the volume too much, I use 'over the ear' type of ear protection (big & cushioned).  What I've found is that I typically need to make numerous adjustments to the buds &/or ear protection to get everything sounding right.  Once I do, that's pretty much it, but getting there sometimes is a pain.  ALL IN ALL:  Highly recommended.  The pros really outweigh the cons!

author: Philip
title: Recommended
content: Sound, comfort, and feel. Firstly, noise isolation is wonderful (although I have no previous reference group to compare to, I still find it great). The sound when gaming or listening to streams is a bit tinny to me, but when listening to music the bass seems to kick in wonderfully and seems to produce a deep, full sound--so much so I had my wife come over when I was testing it because it sounded so great. Comfort at first was an issue with these ear buds but after changing out the size of the in-ear rubberized pieces to a smaller one, it felt much better. Previously the in-ears would stick out just a bit too far and the metal pieces on the back of the ear bud would rest pushing against my auricle which after an hour or so of use would begin to cause discomfort. This was ameliorated by using the smaller in-ear rubber pieces, though. The tangle-free cord is absolutely great, the color combination (red/black) looks great, and the overall construction feels strong and reliable. I wish the cord was just a bit longer, but I knew all that before purchasing.

author: clp.eng
title: bentron DC950 compared to JLabs J5
content:
I'm about to do some traveling & decided I better get a 2nd set of earbuds just in case. I wanted to buy the JLabs J5 again but it is no longer available. After looking around at the bewildering number of choices, these seemed to be similar specs & in my price range.

I use these mostly for videos & some music. I am usually static so I can't comment on how they would perform during very physical activities. I use them on my phone & Kindle.

The sound quality is very similar to the J5 I've been using for a couple of years which means subjectively they sound pretty good for earbuds.

I felt the ear cushions on the DC950 are too "stiff" & not as comfortable as the J5's. The J5's cord is much lighter & thinner (though 1 did fail & was replaced under warranty) than "bentron" cord. Since I'm just sitting there it hasn't been a problem. The DC950 is definitely heavier all the way round.

I still prefer the J5's but since I can't get them any more, I think the DC950 will do a good job & for the price, I would recommend them.

author: Emanuel Jacques
title: Extremely Good Pair of Headphones
content:
Now ive tried dozens of head phones. For the past 3 years, I reached a point in my life where I had to constantly buy a new headphone every month. Whether its at Walmart or Amazon, the headphones would just loose sound or the cable would tear apart from twisting in a pocket, getting snagged on a door knob, or being used while alseep.

Lately I tried to search for headphones that market themselves as durable. Last few pairs I tried were from Amazon. "CHSMONB Bass Stereo Earbuds Headphones" absolutely weak headphones, didnt last two weeks. Returned it after giving it a deservinv negative review. "Kinden Durable Headphones" had similar issues. Complete waste with an awkward design. Explicitly labeled as durable. It's trash. The "Anker SoundBuds Verve" was even worse. I was overwhelmed by frustration. I thought to myself; theres nothing good out there.

But these, these are good. I bought it about over a month ago and thought to myself within ten minutes of use, this might be what i've needed all this time. The flat cable design is brilliant, the elbow port is perfect for using a device stowed in a pocket since it redirects the cabling to avoid tension. The earbuds are fantastic. And the cable is remarkably durable for a flat cable and they definately do resist tge wear a rounded cable would have snap under. It also makes it super easier to detangle.

As I sat around using these headphones that have saved me the hassle, i came to realize a positive review was due. Im even a planning on buying extras.

author: Ophicleide
title: Solid Bass, Clear Sound
content:
I needed a replacement set of headphones for my MP3 player.  I tried a number of different ones that my friends had, but most of them had something unappealing with them.  The exception were a set that ran $40 and a set of Beltron's similar to these DC950.  For the price, these playback almost as well as the $40 set and better than the original set that came with the MP3 player.
The box comes with three sizes of soft silicone ear pieces.  They fit tight on the earphone post, so changing them out is a bit tricky; but that's good once you wear them in the gym.  They set in the ear comfortably and stay set while running on the treadmill.
Overall, the Beltron units a good value for their price... clear sound production, nice strong bass (which is missing in most earbuds in this price range), and comfortable fit.

author: DG
title: Better than advertised
content:
First I ordered the Betron BS-10 earphones with extra base, which was true; however, they were not entirely noise-canceling but they still deserved "Editor's Choice" as they were as-advertised on Amazon. No complaints at all.
I then ordered 2 Betron DC950 earphones for myself and my wife. They are also excellent and in fact, I ordered one more as a spare.  Why?  Although the base is not quite as evident as the BS-10, the noise canceling seems to enhance the quality range fidelity by eliminating external sound influences, and the treble frequencies seem a little better for voice frequencies. Bottom line: Both earphones are great fidelity products, and well constructed. I prefer the DC950 because of the flat, no tangle cord (which really is true!) and the 90-degree angled jack. Both earphones fit snugly into the ears, especially if you loop the cord over the top of your ear. The BS-10 has about a 10-15 degree angle on the bud to perhaps enter the ear canal better, while the DC950 is conventionally straight. Both earbuds fit more or less flush and don't protrude externally = nice designs. It is sort of a toss-up, but for the reasons above, I chose the DC950 for my spare buds. Either way, you will not be disappointed in the excellent construction and fidelity quality.

author: Alexei Khavaev
title: Betron DC950  vs Panasonic RP-HJE120
content:
I use both headphones to listen to music during sport/activity, so the comparative review is from such perspective.

Music quality:
Panasonic has a decent sound - both bass and highs are clear enough. So far, Panasonic are the best among other headphones I had in this price range. Betron is sealing completely air-tight to the ear canal and as a results had pronounced muddy bass drowning the rest of the frequency range.

Wear comfort:
The air-tight fit of Betron I mentioned above makes it rather uncomfortable, it is ironic that despite it Betron headphones are easier to fall from the ear than Panasonic. I’ve been trying various sizes of included ear-buds yet the result is the same.

Convenience for sport/activity:
Betron has tangle free cord, which does tangles less than Panasonic, but the cord is heavy so when you are running the cord yanks the headphones making thumping sound. Both Panasonic and Betron cords have rubberized feeling and tend to catch on the clothing. Also the ear-bud pieces on Betron fall off too easy when wiped and hard to put back - should be the other way around. On Panasonic it is equally easy off and on, not ideal but better than Betron.

Durability:
I had this Panasonic model for quite a while (three pairs) and can tell that the cord is well made and well attached to the buds, but the diaphragm fell off after few hundred hours of use - not a big deal considering the price. I didn’t use Betron long enough to judge its longevity, but it feels well made, slightly better than Panasonic.

Price:
Panasonic is slightly cheaper than Betron.

Conclusion:
Panasonic is better than Betron in almost every aspect, but still have shortcomings, so I’ll be trying other brands…

These do have pronounced bass but at the expense of losing clarity. I don’t like how bulky and heavy they feel in my ears; also, the cord is kind of thick and sticks to itself which is annoying. These will be a back-up pair for listening to podcasts.

author: Picturemike
title: Good for price point,  not true noise cancelling
content:
PROS: economic, sounds great,  average +bass,
CONS: NOT TRUE noise cancelling (there are no electronics to cancel ambient room noise. I did now expect that at a $12 price point), NO microphone  (if you needed that,  I do not need).

author: B.H. Gonzalez
title: They're not great. Keep looking.
content: These headphones are decent in sound. They are not the best quality, but they are pretty loud. Noise cancellation is a bit much for what they offer. They don't have the volume or skip buttons as the description said they would. I could forgive all that and gladly keep them if it wasn't for the fact that they easily pop out of the jack. Any little movement causes the audio jack to pop out, and it's so frustrating because I play loud music to disconnect. If I can't break from everything, my mind feels like it'll split, and I will be in a very bad place mentally.

author: LM
title: Best headphones for the money
content: Sounds quality is excellent. Noise cancellation (once you find the inserts that fit) works well. They give you a carrying case which is a nice touch. This is a must buy if you want great sound for a little money.

author: Amazon Customer
title: So far, so good
content: I'm new to working out and using headphones.  My gym has headphone jacks so you can listen to TV/music. These headphones had good reviews, so I bought them. I wore them for the first time yesterday while jogging. They seem fine. They didn't hurt my ears. The no-tangle cords seem nice (although a little bulky).

author: Julie A. Slagle
title: Great!
content: Love they're tangle-free!

author: Peter B.
title: "Give Your Ears a Treat"
content:
First of all they arrived on the exact same day they promised.
Secondly, when I put them on and began listening to my favorite tunes I couldn't believe the crispness of the highs and the resonance of the lows. A fantastic piece of micro-engineering. I highly recommend these ear-buds to anyone interested in listening to high-end reproductions. Add to all that, it's a great buy..

author: Amazon Customer
title: Doesn't tangle, Multiple ear pads allowed me to find ones that fitted my narrow passages.
content: Computer, pad and vehicles most use

author: William J. Kent
title: The quality of Betron
content: I like everything about them.  The fit in my ears.  The quality of the sound.  They are really built great.  I will buy another pair in the future.

author: Wake Rider
title: Bam Earbuds
content: Ease of use

author: Kelley D.
title: Great sound quality for a reasonable price
content: These are very good quality earphones, and the price is great. I wasn’t expecting much based on the price, but I’m very impressed.

author: C. Walbrun
title: So far ok
content:
Pro:
-  Sound quality is goodThe sound is pretty good on these.
-  Ear plug nubs work nicely
-  Build quality seems good

Con:
-  The wire is too thick and snags on things, despite its design being for "taggle free" it causes some additional tangles. -  The rubber nubs included don't stay in your ear, they slowly fall out
-  Ear plug nubs get kinda gross over time

author: jackie
title: Good sound quality
content: Great sound for the money. I also like the L-shaped plug on this set better than straight plugs because the L-shaped plugs last longer (the straight ones seem to get loose wires quickly)

author: Xen Tsiu
title: cheap yet decent sounding headphones
content: I needed headphones for an exam that required listening to heart and lung sounds. these headphones were cheap and shipped with prime, so I bought them. the sound quality is decent for the price, but don't expect anything phenomenal. 2 years later and I'm still using them for night time listening when my wife is asleep.

author: Maxley Brooks III
title: A great mic/earbud
content: It's great and so far tough. Most of my earbuds start malfunctioning within a month but these have held up great. Also the mic thing is great for gaming.

author: Linda Redamonti
title: They are worth purchasing
content: The quality is very nice on this product, and they are affordable.

author: toni cleveland
title: For the price it is very good
content: This was a good purchase. I had similar costing ten times more but I was loosing them often. This is very good for what I need

author: jeffrey
title: good
content: price good little hallow echo sound during workouts.

author: Amazon Customer
title: N
content: Decent headphones for the price. Good sound. No mic though.

author: E.J.T
title: works great
content: was uncomfortable for my ears.

author: Amazon Customer
title: A
content: He love them

author: Jake
title: Package was obviously opened and returned  l
content:
I dislike them after the first couple uses because it would trigger the Google assistant randomly. I was able to get it to stop erroring out the second time I used them. This is probanly why i reveied an obvious return.

Sound quality 7/10 considering they are ear buds.

Product quality 5/10 for bringing up google assitant when not prompted (thus interrupring the music)

I think its ridiculous that i paid full price for an obviously opened/returned package of "new" head phones

I would not recommend them  because the package was torn up when i opened the box and it caused repeated errors on my phone (the unwarranted google assistant).

The only good thing is the buds fit well in mg ears, are somewhat inexpensive, and sound quality is middle of the road.

Would not recommend and i would like a refund or partial refund because  of these iasues

I do not recommend buying these.

author: Smitty
title: Hassle free cord
content: I hate earbuds with cords that always seem to get tangled up no matter how carefully you wrap them up.  The cords are designed so that they don't easily tangle.  Sound is very good considering the price.  Would definitely buy them again.

author: Jason P. Phrogge
title: Great sound
content: Dynamic range and frequency response is nearly as good as my floor standing home theater speakers. Impressive. Bass response is very good.  comfortable to wear.  Really like the no tangle wires.

author: EdwinW
title: Awesome product
content: love these

author: Mary W
title: .  Arrive Broke
content: They arrive with left ear not working. I would not recommend them AT ALL.

author: rene s corea II
title: For the price you can complain  @ all. They sound  really  good
content: They sound  great

author: LuvBritTV
title: Not worth the price
content: I buy a lot of ear buds.  For whatever reason, the left ear always seems to die.  Most have been pretty decent quality for the same price as these (i.e. Phillips) but these are pretty horrible.  The sound is poor.  The fit is poor.  My suggestion is to try a different brand.

author: Natalie
title: Four Stars
content: good sound; but little fragile construction of earphone itself -- i needed superglue to fix it

author: Hondasan
title: Darn good for the price
content: These earbuds put out a lot of bass. More than any earbuds I have owned. Haven't had them for long, but as of now the best I have purchased from Amazon. They don't have phone compatabitly, so if that is what you are looking for choose something else. If you just want to listen to music or TV, these will fit the bill.

author: Keilyn
title: Good
content: Good

author: Amazon Customer
title: x
content: x

author: Jesus Perez
title: Jack is wonky but good sound quality and durable
content: Sound is good the headphones feel sturdy, but one thing that's does suck is that at least with my galaxy phone the plug of the headphones very easily pops off, making exercising with these headphones or even walking with in your pocket pretty impossible.

author: TheHuppmans
title: Can't beat the price for the quality
content:
For my rating, I was using these in combination with a Yeti microphone for audio and video recording for some web shows and live twitch streams for gaming. I wanted something that didn't cover my entire head and make my head look three times the size it was but was still able to give me great sound quality.

I toss these into the output on my Yeti and use the earpieces that were adjusted for my canals. The sound quality was great. The noise cancellation was so-so. I'm more or less feel like because I was able to fit them in my entire ear canal that it just stopped me from hearing more on the outside. I would assume that if I was in a louder area I could still probably hear people in the background. However in my studio of my house, it wasnt an issue.

Overall I would recommend and buy again

author: Peter
title: Good so far
content: I am not a audiophile, so the earphones do exactly what I expected them to do. The non-tangle wire is very nice because I had problems with other earphones where they twist and wires get exposed.

author: Eric Jenkins
title: Great sound, horrible fit!
content: I received these yesterday and the first thing I noticed was the great sound. The second thing I noticed was the horrible fit, these earbuds tend to fall out of my ears constantly.

author: Susan
title: Great sound
content: Like that the cords don’t get tangled up

author: ladybug
title: Great for the price
content: Great earbuds for the price!  Only complaint is how hard it is to change the size of rubber stoppers.  Great sound though.

author: Amazon Customer
title: very nice product
content:
I have been through many earbuds, they either break, speakers blow or the quality is bad. I was really surprised by these. the packaging was impressive. They seem very well made. i listen to music with pretty heavy bass so i was very surprised when these could handle it. Sound quality is pretty good for the price I would recommend these for people who want a quality earbud for a decent price. I wanted to try a cheaper version of these brand earbuds before spending money on more expensive ones. i will for sure be buying more.

Update
I was very disappointed when i went to listen to music and one of the earbuds no longer works. Not sure what happened because i keep them in the case. I really liked these headphones but i am not sure i will be purchasing these anymore just because they up and quit for no reason. I guess the search continues....

author: Andrew N.
title: Hard to beat for $12.99
content: My workplace is extremely loud, the foam tips for these headphones work fairly well as earplugs. Sound quality is great for the price, the volume control and microphone are conveniently placed and the cord is durable. These are comfortable to wear throughout the day and have worked wonderfully for the past five months.

author: Chris435
title: Sound out of one ear after a month
content: not very durable.  They were great at first and i'll admit the sound quality is great (excellent bass).  After a month, I lost sound in the right plug.  Durability matters.

author: KP
title: Good sound but cable separated
content: Lasted 37 days and then the cable separated from the right ear bud. Sound was good. But like many others they didn’t last long.

author: Amazon Customer
title: Great buds
content: I'm a pro concert audio engineer with 30 years experience who's been around the world several times on tour with everything from rock to acoustic. I was pleasantly surprised at the sound quality of these buds. They're comfortable to wear and very light weight. The frequency response is excellent. It's been my experience with many other ear buds that when they say "Bass driven" or something similar, the response is skewed to make hip hop, pop and other bass heavy music sound cool to those who may not appreciate accurate response. The bass response on these is right where it should be. Music sounds correct. I would definitely buy these again. Spot on Betron from a yank who knows the difference :)

author: Amazon Customer
title: Betron DC950 Headphones
content: These are excellent earbuds, nice Bass and very good clarity. plus comfort. Even though I went for the free shipping they arrived in two days.

author: Gina
title: Really happy with these earphones.
content: My newest earphones have terrible sound quality when I use them on my iPod, and not great when I use them on my computer so decided to take advantage of one the daily deals on Amazon.  These were highly rated so decided to take a chance.  They are great!  The sound quality is really really good, and they block out a lot of the "outside" noise.  And love that they don't tangle.

author: Grace
title: Sound awful
content: They sound terrible and muffled. Also, when you put them in they sound staticky. Definitely did not live up to the good reviews.

author: Lisa Givens
title: Useful
content: Only used them a few times but they are good sturdy headphones
